  "_comment_1": "Phase 5b core coverage ratchet — mirrors .strict-null-budget pattern. Keys are repo-root-relative POSIX paths matching jest.core.config.cjs collectCoverageFrom. Values are pct numbers from coverage-core/coverage-summary.json. PRs that change any number must restamp this file (`npm run check:core-coverage-budget -- --write`).",
  "_comment_2": "Values measured by `npm run test:coverage:core` against the targeted testMatch enumerated in jest.core.config.cjs (19 test files, 547 tests, ~85s). Same testMatch runs locally and in CI, so numbers are deterministic across environments — no first-run restamp is required.",
  "_comment_3_jest30_restamp": "Re-stamped on jest 29 → 30 bump (PR #730). Jest 30 ships an updated Istanbul instrumenter that detects more branches in some files. 9 of 15 files saw branch coverage RISE under the new instrumentation; one file (GovernanceService.ts) saw branch coverage DROP from 26.53% to 21.7% — same 16 tests in tests/unit/services/ai/orchestrator/GovernanceService.commit2.test.ts run and pass, the denominator just got larger (28 covered / 129 total). This is an instrumentation artifact, not a removed test or refactor regression — exercising the documented escape hatch in CLAUDE.md's core-coverage-budget policy.",
